      "value": "Julian Union High is a very small high school district in eastern San Diego County, with about 22 students who have an IEP. The number of autistic students is small enough that the state does not report it separately, so this profile describes all students with disabilities rather than autism specifically. About 68% of students with disabilities spend most of the school day in a general-education classroom."
