      "ai_model": "claude-opus (via Claude Code session)",
      "based_on_sources": [
        "cde_spedps",
        "ca_dashboard"
      ],
      "value": "Because this is a very small district, the state withholds autism-specific counts and several other measures to protect student privacy, so the figures here cover all students with disabilities together. About 68% of students with disabilities are in a general-education classroom for most of the school day. State distance-from-standard test scores were not separately reported for students with disabilities in a district this size. The suspension rate was about 11% for both students with disabilities and the student body overall."
    }
